27/12/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Kresnik Collaku, Tirana's deputy ambassador to the United States, confirmed on Saturday (December 26th) that Albania is ready to accept suspected terrorists who have been housed in the US detention facility at Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.
He did not however, specify the exact number of prisoners Tirana would take.
On January 22nd, US President Barack Obama said the Guantanamo prison "will be closed no later than one year from now".
(MRT, Voice of America - 26/12/09;
BBC - 22/01/09)
